Cook beef in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until brown; drain. Stir in hot water, milk, uncooked Pasta, Sauce Mix, broccoli, cauliflower and carrots and Italian seasoning. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in peas. Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until pasta is tender. Stir in sour cream; sprinkle with cheese.